headline: A Look at Starbucks’s Valuation as $1 Billion Restructuring Plan Unfolds
summary: Starbucks (SBUX) is drawing fresh attention from investors after unveiling a $1 billion North American restructuring plan, which includes targeted store closures, corporate workforce reductions, and new AI-driven initiatives to improve operational efficiency. Alongside these strategic changes, the company approved a modest quarterly dividend increase while facing continued scrutiny from shareholders regarding labor negotiations and union discussions. headline: Starbucks poised to hire around 8K assistant mangers
summary: The chain is testing the assistant manager role — a step between hourly shift supervisor and salaried manager — at 62 stores to fine-tune the position before expanding it to nearly all U.S. and Canadian stores.
